Intersection of Technology and Human Nature  
\-How technology can exploit human vulnerabilities  
\-Examples of cognitive biases being manipulated (e.g., social influence, group dynamics)

Ethical Concerns in Technology Design  
\-The problem with "giving people what they want"  
\-Uncontrolled psychological experiments through A/B testing  
\-Potential for manipulation and exploitation at scale

Humane Technology Approach  
\-Designing technology that respects human vulnerabilities  
\-Focusing on users' values and goals rather than engagement metrics  
\-Enabling users to make wise choices

Call to Action for Technologists  
\-Importance of understanding human psychology and neuroscience  
\-Shifting paradigms in technology design and development  
\-Using tools like the Humane Tech Design Guide to assess products

